@node Features
@chapter Features

@cindex Features

@itemize
@item
Transient menu interface to control @strong{Music app}.

@code{M-x} @code{now-playing-tmenu}

@item
Display the current playing track in the mini-buffer.

@code{M-x} @code{now-playing-current-track}

@item
Periodically poll the @strong{Music app} to display the current track in the mini-buffer.

@code{M-x} @code{now-playing-start-polling-current-track}

When polling is turned on@comma{} an in-memory log is kept in the special buffer @code{✱now playing log✱}. It can be opened with the command @code{now-playing-find-log}.

Polling can be stopped with the command @code{now-playing-cancel-polling}.

@item
Uses Emacs @code{ns-do-applescript} to directly call AppleScript for performance.
@end itemize

@node Install
@chapter Install

@cindex Install

@strong{Now Playing} is available to install from MELPA (TBD).

Manual installation can be done by ensuring that @code{now-playing.el} is available in the Emacs @code{load-path} variable.

The Transient interface and commands for polling are auto-loaded so no configuration is necessary. That said@comma{} users might find it convenient to make a keybinding to the Transient menu @code{now-playing-tmenu} as follows:

@lisp
(keymap-global-set "<f14>" #'now-playing-tmenu)
@end lisp

The keybinding itself can be set to user preference.

@node Commands
@chapter Commands

@cindex Commands

The primary interface for @strong{Now Playing} is the Transient menu @code{now-playing-tmenu}. It can be invoked via @code{execute-extended-command} @kbd{M-x}.

Listed below are commands to both control or get current information from the Music app.

@table @asis
@item now-playing-tmenu
Transient menu for @strong{Now Playing}.
@vindex now-playing-tmenu

@image{images/now-playing-screenshot,,,,png}

The following commands are provided:

@itemize
@item
Pause/Play (@code{SPC}@comma{} ▶/⏸)
@item
Previous (@code{p}@comma{} ⏮) and Next (@code{n}@comma{} ⏭) Track
@item
Open (launch) Music app (@code{o}@comma{} ♫)
@item
Increase (@code{<up>}) and Decrease (@code{<down>}) volume
@item
Refresh current track (@code{r}@comma{} ⟲)
@end itemize
@end table


@table @asis
@item now-playing-set-state
Set Music app playback state.
@vindex now-playing-set-state

@item now-playing-play
Play Music app.
@vindex now-playing-play

Note if there is no current track@comma{} this AppleScript command will not succeed. If this occurs@comma{} switch to the Music app to directly select a track to play.

@item now-playing-pause
Pause Music app.
@vindex now-playing-pause

@item now-playing-playpause
Toggle play or pause Music app.
@vindex now-playing-playpause

Note if there is no current track@comma{} this AppleScript command will not succeed. If this occurs@comma{} switch to the Music app to directly select a track to play.

@item now-playing-stop
Stop Music app.
@vindex now-playing-stop

Note this command will deselect the current track in the Music app@comma{} making the commands @code{now-playing-play} and @code{now-playing-playpause} ineffective. If this occurs@comma{} switch to the Music app and select a track to resume expected behavior.

@item now-playing-next-track
Next track Music app.
@vindex now-playing-next-track

Note if this command is called when on the last track of the playlist or album will deselect the current track.

@item now-playing-previous-track
Previous track Music app.
@vindex now-playing-previous-track

Note if this command is called when on the first track of the playlist or album will deselect the current track.

@item now-playing-get-volume
Get Music app sound volume.
@vindex now-playing-get-volume

@item now-playing-set-volume
Set Music app sound volume to ARG@.
@vindex now-playing-set-volume

@item now-playing-increase-volume
Increase Music app sound volume.
@vindex now-playing-increase-volume

@item now-playing-decrease-volume
Decrease Music app sound volume.
@vindex now-playing-decrease-volume

@item now-playing-current-track
Get current track on Music app.
@vindex now-playing-current-track

@item now-playing-launch-music
Launch Music app.
@vindex now-playing-launch-music
@end table

@subsubheading Command Variables

The following customizable variables can be changed to preference:

@table @asis
@item now-playing-volume-delta
Change increment for sound volume (default 5).
@vindex now-playing-volume-delta

@item now-playing-dismiss-menu-for-playpause
If non-nil@comma{} then toggling pause/play ▶/⏸ will dismiss the Transient menu
@code{now-playing-tmenu}.
@vindex now-playing-dismiss-menu-for-playpause
@end table

